gomodel:SYNGO_1008  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: The location of the adenosine A2A receptor was assessed by pre-embedding immunoperoxidase and immunogold labelling. The A2A receptor was found in some axons and axon terminals (Table1 and 2, Fig.2-6). Immunoreactivity was found on plasma membranes.\n\nA monoclonal, mouse, antiserum was raised against the human adenosine A2A receptor (clone 7F6-G5-A2, Upstate USA, Charlotteswville, VA). The antibody produced the same immunoreactivity pattern in wildtype mice, but not in A2A KO mice (data not shown in this paper).. Experimental description: Six adult male Sprague-Dawleyrats (200-250 g; Taconic Farms, Germantown, NY) weredeeply anesthetized by..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
